/-!
Restrict a component of finite symmetric difference to a set family over a finite type.
The resulting set family consists of sets of the form (A ∆ B) ∩ C, where C is the original set.
This operation is designed to be used with set families that have a finite symmetric difference structure.
-/
noncomputable def restrictFiniteSymmDiffComponent (𝓒 : Finset (Set α)) :
    Finset (Set α) :=
  Finset.image (fun A => A ∆ ⋂ B ∈ 𝓒, B) 𝓒

